  1→# Intent Node: Data Models
  2→
  3→## SurrealDB Schema
  4→
  5→### intent table
  6→
  7→```sql
  8→DEFINE TABLE intent SCHEMAFULL;
  9→
 10→-- Core fields
 11→DEFINE FIELD goal ON intent TYPE string;
 12→DEFINE FIELD reasoning ON intent TYPE string;
 13→DEFINE FIELD status ON intent TYPE string
 14→  ASSERT $value IN ["draft", "pending_auth", "pending_veto", "authorized", "executing", "completed", "vetoed", "failed"];
 15→DEFINE FIELD priority ON intent TYPE int
 16→  ASSERT $value >= 0 AND $value <= 100;
 17→
 18→-- Action specification (what the agent wants to do)
 19→DEFINE FIELD action_spec ON intent TYPE object;
 20→DEFINE FIELD action_spec.provider ON intent TYPE string;
 21→DEFINE FIELD action_spec.action ON intent TYPE string;
 22→DEFINE FIELD action_spec.params ON intent TYPE option<object>;
 23→
 24→-- Budget constraint
 25→DEFINE FIELD budget_limit ON intent TYPE option<object>;
 26→DEFINE FIELD budget_limit.amount ON intent TYPE float;
 27→DEFINE FIELD budget_limit.currency ON intent TYPE string;
 28→
 29→-- Evaluation result (populated by authorizer)
 30→DEFINE FIELD evaluation ON intent TYPE option<object>;
 31→DEFINE FIELD evaluation.decision ON intent TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["APPROVE", "REJECT"];
 32→DEFINE FIELD evaluation.risk_score ON intent TYPE int ASSERT $value >= 0 AND $value <= 100;
 33→DEFINE FIELD evaluation.reason ON intent TYPE string;
 34→DEFINE FIELD evaluation.evaluated_at ON intent TYPE datetime;
 35→DEFINE FIELD evaluation.policy_only ON intent TYPE bool;
 36→
 37→-- Veto window
 38→DEFINE FIELD veto_expires_at ON intent TYPE option<datetime>;
 39→DEFINE FIELD veto_reason ON intent TYPE option<string>;
 40→
 41→-- Error tracking
 42→DEFINE FIELD error_reason ON intent TYPE option<string>;
 43→
 44→-- Traceability
 45→DEFINE FIELD trace_id ON intent TYPE string;
 46→DEFINE FIELD requester ON intent TYPE record<identity>;
 47→DEFINE FIELD workspace ON intent TYPE record<workspace>;
 48→DEFINE FIELD created_at ON intent TYPE datetime;
 49→DEFINE FIELD updated_at ON intent TYPE option<datetime>;
 50→DEFINE FIELD expiry ON intent TYPE option<datetime>;
 51→
 52→-- Indexes
 53→DEFINE INDEX intent_workspace_status ON intent FIELDS workspace, status;
 54→DEFINE INDEX intent_created_at ON intent FIELDS created_at;
 55→DEFINE INDEX intent_trace_id ON intent FIELDS trace_id;
 56→DEFINE INDEX intent_veto_expires ON intent FIELDS veto_expires_at;
 57→```
 58→
 59→### Relations
 60→
 61→```sql
 62→-- Intent triggered by a task (intent originates from task assignment)
 63→DEFINE TABLE triggered_by TYPE RELATION IN intent OUT task SCHEMAFULL;
 64→DEFINE FIELD created_at ON triggered_by TYPE datetime;
 65→
 66→-- Intent gates an agent session (authorized intent enables session)
 67→DEFINE TABLE gates TYPE RELATION IN intent OUT agent_session SCHEMAFULL;
 68→DEFINE FIELD created_at ON gates TYPE datetime;
 69→
 70→-- Human vetoed an intent
 71→DEFINE TABLE vetoed_by TYPE RELATION IN identity OUT intent SCHEMAFULL;
 72→DEFINE FIELD reason ON vetoed_by TYPE string;
 73→DEFINE FIELD vetoed_at ON vetoed_by TYPE datetime;
 74→```
 75→
 76→### SurrealQL EVENT
 77→
 78→```sql
 79→-- Fire on transition TO pending_auth (not on every update)
 80→DEFINE EVENT intent_pending_auth ON intent
 81→  WHEN $before.status != "pending_auth" AND $after.status = "pending_auth"
 82→  THEN {
 83→    http::post(
 84→      "http://127.0.0.1:{PORT}/api/intents/" + <string> meta::id($after.id) + "/evaluate",
 85→      $after,
 86→      { "Content-Type": "application/json" }
 87→    );
 88→  };
 89→```
 90→
 91→Note: The `{PORT}` placeholder is replaced with the actual server port in the migration. The event uses `$before.status != "pending_auth"` as an idempotent guard to prevent double-firing.
 92→
 93→### Authority Scope Extensions
 94→
 95→```sql
 96→-- New actions for intent lifecycle
 97→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "code_agent", action: "create_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
 98→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "code_agent", action: "submit_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
 99→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "architect", action: "create_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
100→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "architect", action: "submit_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
101→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "management", action: "create_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
102→CREATE authority_scope CONTENT { agent_type: "management", action: "submit_intent", permission: "auto", created_at: time::now() };
103→```
104→
105→Human identity types get implicit `veto_intent` permission (checked at route level via identity.type = 'human').
106→
107→## TypeScript Types
108→
109→### Intent Domain Types (types.ts)
110→
111→```
112→IntentStatus = "draft" | "pending_auth" | "pending_veto" | "authorized"
113→             | "executing" | "completed" | "vetoed" | "failed"
114→
115→ActionSpec = { provider: string, action: string, params?: Record<string, unknown> }
116→
117→BudgetLimit = { amount: number, currency: string }
118→
119→EvaluationResult = { decision: "APPROVE" | "REJECT", risk_score: number, reason: string }
120→
121→RoutingDecision =
122→  | { route: "auto_approve" }
123→  | { route: "veto_window", expires_at: Date }
124→  | { route: "reject", reason: string }
125→
126→IntentRecord = {
127→  id: RecordId<"intent", string>
128→  goal: string
129→  reasoning: string
130→  status: IntentStatus
131→  priority: number
132→  action_spec: ActionSpec
133→  budget_limit?: BudgetLimit
134→  evaluation?: EvaluationResult & { evaluated_at: Date, policy_only: boolean }
135→  veto_expires_at?: Date
136→  veto_reason?: string
137→  error_reason?: string
138→  trace_id: string
139→  requester: RecordId<"identity", string>
140→  workspace: RecordId<"workspace", string>
141→  created_at: Date
142→  updated_at?: Date
143→  expiry?: Date
144→}
145→```
146→
147→### Status Transition Map
148→
149→```
150→draft          -> pending_auth
151→pending_auth   -> pending_veto | authorized | vetoed | failed
152→pending_veto   -> authorized | vetoed
153→authorized     -> executing
154→executing      -> completed | failed
155→```
156→
157→Invalid transitions return an error value (not exception).
158→
159→## Graph Traversal Patterns
160→
161→### Audit trail query (task -> outcome)
162→```sql
163→SELECT
164→  id, goal, status, evaluation,
165→  <-triggered_by<-task AS originating_task,
166→  ->gates->agent_session AS spawned_session,
167→  <-vetoed_by<-identity AS vetoed_by_identity
168→FROM intent
169→WHERE workspace = $workspace
170→ORDER BY created_at DESC;
171→```
172→
173→### Pending intents for governance feed
174→```sql
175→SELECT id, goal, status, evaluation, veto_expires_at, created_at, priority,
176→  action_spec.provider AS provider,
177→  action_spec.action AS action_name
178→FROM intent
179→WHERE workspace = $workspace
180→AND status IN ["pending_veto"]
181→ORDER BY priority DESC, created_at ASC;
182→```
183→
184→## Feed Integration
185→
186→Intent items map to `GovernanceFeedItem`:
187→
188→| Intent State | Feed Tier | Actions |
189→|-------------|-----------|---------|
190→| pending_veto (risk > 30) | blocking | veto, discuss |
191→| vetoed | awareness | discuss |
192→| failed (evaluation_timeout) | review | discuss |
193→
194→The `GovernanceFeedAction` type is extended with `"veto"` action. The `EntityKind` type in contracts.ts is extended with `"intent"`.
